asyncplusplus
------------------------------------------
Async++ is a lightweight concurrency framework for C++11. The concept was
inspired by the Microsoft PPL library and the N3428 C++ standard proposal.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.4-1
  libasync++-devel-1.2-1bl1
  libasync++1-1.2-1bl1
  libgcc1-12.4.0-3
  libstdc++6-12.4.0-3
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cmake-3.28.3-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  ninja-1.12.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/Amanieu/asyncplusplus

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/Amanieu/asyncplusplus/archive/refs/tags/v1.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack asyncplusplus-1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./asyncplusplus-1.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/asyncplusplus-1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/asyncplusplus-1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libasync++1-1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libasync++-devel-1.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(asyncplusplus)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/asyncplusplus.README
  /usr/share/doc/asyncplusplus/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/asyncplusplus/README.md

(libasync++1)
  /usr/bin/cygasync++-1.dll

(libasync++-devel)
